DRAWN BUTTER Drawn butter is melted butter , often served as a sauce for steamed seafood .
Some cooks restrict the term to clarified butter ; while others insist that it should not be clarified .
When it is served with seafood , diners often add lemon juice to it .
DRAWN BUTTER SAUCES Section::::Drawn butter sauces .
In the 18th century , a small amount of flour and water or milk was often added to melted butter to thicken it and prevent it from separating .
Later in the 19th century , increasing amounts of flour and water were used .
These sauces may themselves be named simply " melted butter " , " drawn butter " , or " drawn butter sauce " , and flavored with vinegar , salt , pepper , capers , watercress , and so on .
